# NEMETIC STRING
# #F026 Kindergarten AI Commons
# term_id: F026
# Generated: 2026-05-20

Φ(kindergarten_ai_commons) = λ(vector-liberatory-capability) ∘ β(generate-peer-production) ∘ ρ(attune-collective-imagination) ∘ μ(reduce-institutional-dependency) ∘ Z(permeable) + ε | :commons-emergence

# SIML encoding:
# ⟨Narrative|post-capital-capability-emergence⟩ ⇄ ⟨Actor|distributed-creative-agency⟩

# Plain reading:
# The pattern names AI capability as a commons-forming pressure: competitive capital distributes cognitive infrastructure widely enough that peer production, collective imagination, and local execution become newly reachable outside institutional bottlenecks.
# It is not techno-utopian inevitabilism; permeability and stewardship decide whether capability becomes commons or capture.
